fetchLatestPosition(int256,uint256,uint2.details: fetches new user's position after liquidation. The new liquidated position's debt is decreased by 0.01% to make sure that branch's liquidity never becomes 0 as if it would have gotten 0 then there will be multiple cases that we would need to tackle.

params.positionRawDebt_: position's raw debt when it was last updated through operate
params.positionTickId_: position's tick Id. This stores the debt factor and branch to make the first connection
params.positionTick_: position's tick when it was last updated through operate
params.tickData_: position's tick's tickData just for minor comparison to know if data is moved to tick Id or is still in tick data

returns._0: final tick position after all the liquidation
returns._1: final debt of position after all the liquidation
returns.branchData_: final branch's data where the position is at currently
returns.branchId_: final branch's ID where the position is at currently
returns.positionRawCol_: final collateral of position after all the liquidation

liquidate(uint256,uint256,address,bool).details: allows to liquidate all bad debt of all users at once. Liquidator can also liquidate partially any amount they want.

params.absorb_: if true then liquidate from absorbed first
params.colPerUnitDebt_: minimum collateral token per unit of debt in 1e18 decimals
params.debtAmt_: total debt to liquidate (aka debt token to swap into collateral token)
params.to_: address at which collateral token should go to.            If dead address (0x000000000000000000000000000000000000dEaD) then reverts with custom error "FluidLiquidateResult"            returning the actual collateral and actual debt liquidated. Useful to find max liquidatable amounts via try / catch.

returns.actualColAmt_: total liquidated collateral which liquidator will get
returns.actualDebtAmt_: if liquidator sends debtAmt_ more than debt remaining to liquidate then actualDebtAmt_ changes from debtAmt_ else remains same

liquidityCallback(address,uint256,bytes).details: liquidity callback for cheaper token transfers in case of deposit or payback. only callable by Liquidity during an operation.

operate(uint256,int256,int256,address).details: Single function which handles supply, withdraw, borrow & payback

params.newCol_: new collateral. If positive then deposit, if negative then withdraw, if 0 then do nohing
params.newDebt_: new debt. If positive then borrow, if negative then payback, if 0 then do nohing
params.nftId_: NFT ID for interaction. If 0 then create new NFT/position.
params.to_: address where withdraw or borrow should go. If address(0) then msg.sender

returns._0: nftId_ if 0 then this returns the newly created NFT Id else returns the same NFT ID
returns._1: newCol_ final supply amount. Mainly if max withdraw using type(int).min then this is useful to get perfect amount else remain same as newCol_
returns._2: newDebt_ final borrow amount. Mainly if max payback using type(int).min then this is useful to get perfect amount else remain same as newDebt_

rebalance().details: Checks total supply of vault's in Liquidity Layer & Vault contract and rebalance it accordingly if vault supply is more than Liquidity Layer then deposit difference through reserve/rebalance contract if vault supply is less than Liquidity Layer then withdraw difference to reserve/rebalance contract if vault borrow is more than Liquidity Layer then borrow difference to reserve/rebalance contract if vault borrow is less than Liquidity Layer then payback difference through reserve/rebalance contract

params.vaultVariables2_: exactly same as vaultVariables2 from storage

returns.liqBorrowExPrice_: latest liquidity's borrow token borrow exchange price
returns.liqSupplyExPrice_: latest liquidity's supply token supply exchange price
returns.vaultBorrowExPrice_: latest vault's borrow token exchange price
returns.vaultSupplyExPrice_: latest vault's supply token exchange price

updateExchangePricesOnStorage().details: updating exchange price on storage. Only need to update on storage when changing supply or borrow magnifier

updateExchangePrices(uint256).notice: Calculates new vault exchange prices. Does not update values in storage.

updateExchangePricesOnStorage().notice: note admin module is also calling this function self call
